          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688123378369-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> to the dish with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce, tamarind paste</strong>, <strong>pho broth paste</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>your<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>half</strong> your<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>lime leaf[ves] </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir everything together and bring to the boil, then cover and put in the oven for 25-30 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688123383381-x200.jpg",
