          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688123383381-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the stew is in the oven, add your<strong> basmati rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with the <strong>remaining lime leaf[ves]</strong>, <strong>outer lemongrass layers</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>baked rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1688123386762-x200.jpg",
